  "prompt": "Why do I get snapchat notifications of some people but not others?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you receive Snapchat notifications from some people but not others:\n\n1. **Notification Settings**: Your notification settings for individual friends may vary. You might have enabled notifications for some contacts while disabling them for others. Check your Snapchat notification settings to see if they are set up correctly.\n\n2. **Do Not Disturb Mode**: If you have enabled \"Do Not Disturb\" mode on your device or within Snapchat, it may prevent notifications from certain contacts from appearing.\n\n3. **Friendship Status**: If you are not friends with someone on Snapchat, you may not receive notifications for their snaps or messages. Only friends might trigger notifications based on the app's privacy settings.\n\n4. **Privacy Settings**: Some users may have their privacy settings configured to limit who can send them notifications or messages. If a friend has restricted their account, you might not receive notifications from them.\n\n5. **App Permissions**: Ensure that Snapchat has the necessary permissions on your device to send notifications. Check your phone's settings to verify that the app has access to notifications.\n\n6. **Account Settings**: Occasionally, your account settings might inadvertently restrict notifications. Reviewing your overall Snapchat account settings could help resolve any issues.\n\n7. **App Updates/Bugs**: Sometimes, app updates can introduce bugs or issues with settings. Ensure your Snapchat app is updated to the latest version to minimize potential problems.\n\nIf none of these reasons seem to apply, it might be worth reaching out to Snapchat's support for further assistance.",
